    "summary": "I'm passionate about two things: space exploration  and communication. And these two passions lead me into what I do today: I'm a science communicator working for the European Space Agency to increase awareness of the space exploration programme.\n\nI started studying Physics and Astrophysics at University of Florence (Italy) and then a Master in Science Communication at SISSA.\n\nI have learned about the importance of communicating with different targets in different ways and how to use multimedia tools to do that.\n\nI started my career working as science explainer in museums and research institutions to continue as science writer and editor for newspapers and  publishers for schools.\n\nAfter a master thesis in how to communicate science on social media like YouTube I became more interested in how to create multimedia products to disseminate the scientific knowledge and decided to apply for a position in ESA focused on outreach.\n\nMy strengths are passion for my job, creativity and hard work, attention to details, team work and team-managing skills.",
